# Context: a `_gsx` name declared in the SAME top-level Go region as an element
# literal in statement position (`go <b/>`). checkReservedDecls lexes the region
# with go/scanner — it does not parse — so the element literal is just a run of
# tokens the scanner steps over, and `_gsxrt` a few lines on is still reported. A
# parse-based check could not read this region at all: `go <b/>` is not a call, so
# no standalone-Go reconstruction of it parses. `_gsxrt` also happens to be a name
# the generator emits, so catching it here is what replaces the raw
# `_gsxrt already declared through import of package gsx` the skeleton would
# otherwise draw.
-- input.gsx --
package demo

func spawn() {
	go <b/>
}

var _gsxrt = 1

component Uses() {
	<b>hi</b>
}
-- diagnostics.golden --
4:9: expression in go must be function call
7:5: identifier "_gsxrt" uses the reserved _gsx prefix (reserved for generated code)
